Launch 3 Servers with same Keypair & same SecurityGroup

Install jenkins on Master
Install java on both Master & Slave
Port 8080 on controller & Port 22 on both controller, agents
Create jenkins user on both agents with pwd
Install Git on Agents
Generate SSH Key using jenkins user & copy public key to both agents

Dashboard → Manage Jenkins → Nodes → New Node (Add both agents)

Fill in the details:

Node name: agent1
Type: Permanent Agent

Then configure:

Field	Value
Remote root directory	/home/ec2-user/jenkins
Labels	linux
Usage	Use this node as much as possible
Launch method	Launch agents via SSH
Host	172.31.39.71 (your agent private IP)
Credentials	SSH private key of the controller's jenkins user
Host Key Verification Strategy	Non verifying Verification Strategy (for lab/testing) or Known hosts (recommended for production)

Set Disk Space Monitoring Thresholds (Free Disk Space & Temp Space) 

  Note: If we don't set the Agents will go offline due to less space.

Click Save.


Pipeline:

  pipeline {
    agent none

    stages {

        stage('Run on Agent1') {
            agent {
                label 'LinuxAgent1'
            }
            steps {
                sh '''
                    echo "Running on Agent1"
                    hostname
                    whoami
                '''
            }
        }

        stage('Run on Agent2') {
            agent {
                label 'LinuxAgent2'
            }
            steps {
                sh '''
                    echo "Running on Agent2"
                    hostname
                    whoami
                '''
            }
        }
    }
}

Flow:

Controller
----------
Jenkins service
User: jenkins
Private Key:
/var/lib/jenkins/.ssh/id_rsa
        |
        | SSH
        v
Agent
-----
Login user: ec2-user
Authorized key:
/home/ec2-user/.ssh/authorized_keys


Note: since we copied keys to agents in ec2-user dir we need to give obly tgat user in PrivateKey Controller.
